   <text>
      <body>
         <pb n="1r" facs="lf_pDas_1740_brd_ncd_hin_r.jpg"/>
         <div xml:lang="per" type="invocation" xml:id="orig_div1" rend="top centre"><p>ا</p></div>
         <div corresp="#orig_div1" xml:id="transdiv1"><p>Alif</p></div>
         <div xml:id="orig_div2" xml:lang="hin" type="authorisation" rend="top centre"> 
            <p><stamp type="seal"><mentioned><gap></gap></mentioned></stamp></p>
         </div>
         <div corresp="#orig_div2" xml:id="trans_div2"> <p><stamp type="seal">Square black ink seal with a 5-line illegible inscription<mentioned><gap></gap></mentioned></stamp></p></div>
         <div xml:id="orig_div3" xml:lang="hin" type="maintext">
            <p>
               <lb/>राज श्री <persName ref="#gangadhar">पंडत गंगाधरजी</persName> <choice><abbr>बै॰</abbr><expan>बेटा</expan></choice> <persName ref="#sadashivPandit">सदासीवजी</persName> मु-
               <lb/>कासदार <choice><abbr>प्र॰</abbr><expan>परगना</expan></choice> <placeName ref="#pgDhar">धार</placeName> आगे जमा बमुजब तसखीस
               <lb/>राजश्री राव साहबजी <persName rend="elevated" ref="#yashwantRaoPuwar">श्री यासवंतराव पुवार</persName> बमुजब
               <lb/>कबुलीयत <choice><abbr>मु॰</abbr><expan>मुकद्दम</expan></choice> <choice><abbr>मी॰</abbr><expan>मिरजा</expan></choice> <persName ref="#babuKhan">बाबु खा</persName> <choice><abbr>बै॰</abbr><expan>बेटा</expan></choice> फाजलखा <choice><abbr>मौ॰</abbr><expan>मौजा</expan></choice>
               <lb/><placeName ref="#ratnagaon">रतनागावा</placeName> वगर बा॰<note>This word is written as if it is an abbreviation, but the reading of its full form is not clear.</note> <choice><abbr>फ॰</abbr><expan>फसल</expan></choice> खरीफ रबी <choice><abbr>स॰</abbr><expan>सन</expan></choice> <date calendar="#fasli">११५०</date> <choice><abbr>फ॰</abbr><expan>फसली</expan></choice>
               <lb/>का सब दामदाम भर पाया फारखती लीख दीवी
               <lb/>खातीर जमा सु साल आयंदा कीतरु दत कमा-
               <lb/>या करणा
               <lb/><choice><abbr>मौ॰</abbr><expan>मौजा</expan></choice> <placeName ref="#ratnagra">रतनागरो</placeName> <choice><abbr>मौ॰</abbr><expan>मौजा</expan></choice> <placeName ref="#khanpur">खानुपुर</placeName> <choice><abbr>मौ॰</abbr><expan>मौजा</expan></choice> <unclear>अकबपुर</unclear>
               <lb/>छ ९ <del>सन</del> <add>माहे</add> साबान 
            </p>
         </div>
         <div corresp="#orig_div3" xml:id="trans_div3">
            <p>
               <lb/><ref type="glossary" target="#gl_rajashri">Rajashri</ref> <persName ref="#gangadhar">Pandit Gangadharji</persName> son of <persName ref="#sadashivPandit">Sadashivji </persName> <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_mokasadar">mokasadar</ref>
               <lb/>of <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_pargana">pargana</ref> <placeName ref="#pgDhar">Dhar</placeName>, is ordered as follows: the assessed taxes have been received, in accordance with the [official] assessment
               <lb/>of <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_rajashri">Rajashri</ref> Rao Sahibji, <persName rend="elevated" ref="#yashwantRaoPuwar">Yashwant Rao Puwar</persName>,<note>For respect, this name is written in the top right corner of the document.</note> [and] according to the
               <lb/><ref type="glossary" target="#gl_qabuliyat">qabuliyat</ref> of <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_muqaddam">muqaddam</ref> Mirza <persName ref="#babuKhan">Babu Khan</persName>, son of Fazil Khan of
               <lb/>Village <placeName ref="#ratnagaon">Ratnagaon</placeName>,<note>Although spelled differently, this is likely the same place as village <placeName ref="#ratnagra">Ratnagaro</placeName> mentioned below.</note> etc., for the harvests of <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_kharif">Kharif</ref> and <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_rabi">Rabiʿ</ref> for the year 1150 <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_fasli">Fasli</ref>
               <lb/>every coin is received. A <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_farighkhatti">pharkhati</ref> has been written.<note>It is not entirely clear whether this document is the said <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_farighkhatti">pharkhati</ref>, or is about it.</note>
               <lb/>From contentment, how much tribute<note>An alternate reading of दत is gift or endowment.</note>
               <lb/>shall be earned in the coming year.
               <lb/>Village <placeName ref="#ratnagra">Ratnagaro</placeName> Village <placeName ref="#khanpur">Khanpur</placeName> Village <unclear>Akabpur</unclear>
               <lb/>On the <date>9th of Shaʿban</date><note>This last line is written in Modi script. The writer appears to have written the word for "year" by mistake and then crossed it out.</note>
            </p></div>
         <div xml:id="orig_div4" xml:lang="hin" type="authorisation" rend="bottom centre"> 
            <p><stamp type="seal"><mentioned>मोरतब <unclear>सुद</unclear></mentioned></stamp></p></div>
         <div corresp="#orig_div4" xml:id="trans_div4"><p><stamp type="seal">Square black ink seal<mentioned><unclear>It was prepared.</unclear></mentioned></stamp></p></div>
      </body>
